<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="concept_x2j_5ts_g5">
 <title>Configuring LDAP Authentication</title>
 <shortdesc>If your organization uses LDAP, configure <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> to use
        LDAP authentication. After you configure LDAP authentication, users log in to <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> using
        their LDAP username and password. </shortdesc>
 <conbody>
        <p><indexterm>LDAP authentication<indexterm>configuring</indexterm></indexterm>To configure
            LDAP authentication, perform the following tasks:<ol id="ol_dqf_dts_5x">
                <li>Configure LDAP connection information.</li>
                <li>Optionally, configure secure connections to the LDAP server.</li>
                <li>Map LDAP groups to <ph
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                    /> roles.</li>
                <li>Optionally, configure multiple LDAP servers.</li>
                <li>If you use MapR stages, enable LDAP authentication for MapR.</li>
            </ol></p>
    </conbody>
</concept>
